    <note>Cheng(1) Dexuan [17245] He was a good physician and when Zhao(1) Taizong [9002] was prefect of Kaifeng, he was summoned to wait upon the future emperor. When Taizong became emperor, he appointed Dexuan as Hanlin shi. When Chen(1) Hongjin [3067] was returning to allegiance, Taizong ordered Dexuan to meet and escort him. When the boats were crossing the Huai, a violent wind developed and the party was fearful and wanted to turn back. Dexuan said: "I am carrying the ruler's mandate, how can I flee danger. He prayed with a sacrifice of wine and proceeded. The winds and waves stopped. CBD, 4, 3050.</note>
